						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Above it says that if result &lt; 8 or result &gt; $7FF, the DAC receives 0, and the sweep unit won't change the channel's period.</div><br /><br />It doesn't say &quot;result &lt; 8&quot; though, but &quot;current period &lt; 8&quot;. If the current period is &gt;=8 and the result would be &lt;8, then &quot;when the channel's period is less than 8 [...] the sweep unit doesn't change the channel's period&quot; implies that the period would be changed by the sweep unit, while &quot;result &lt; 8&quot; implies that it wouldn't be changed. So which one is it?</div><br />It's what the APU doc says, and not my erroneous paraphrasing in the post above. I don't know all the details of the APU anymore; I have to go by the docs like anyone (perfect example of why redundancy is to be avoided).</div>

