				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I updated my old apu_sweep tests and added them to the wiki.<br /><br />EDIT: added test that checks minimum period behavior. It's as documented. If channel's raw period &lt; 8, then channel's DAC receives 0 and sweep won't modify channel's period. This the only minimum period behavior; it doesn't matter whether the shifter result &lt; 8. All this is verified by the test so try implementing the alternative interpretations you can come up with and see whether they pass.</div>

					
