						<div class="postbody">If only it did, then these tests wouldn't require listening. Only the length counter reaching 0 affects $4015 read. Basically a channel has many things that can force the DAC to receive 0 (which letting everything else in the channel continue to run -- less hardware to achieve this). This silencing is one of them. I need to learn how to read those decaps so I can look at the circuit that achieves this.</div>

