			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Looking at Visual 2A03 the wiki seems a bit off in some of the descriptions, though the visible behavior might still be equivalent (and to be fair the wiki only claims to present an &quot;abstract model&quot;).<br /><br />For example, <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter</a><!-- m --> says that the length counter is forced to zero when disabling a channel via $4015, but it actually seems to be unaffected. Rather, each channel has an <em>enabled</em> bit (from $4015) and an <em>active</em> bit (e.g. sq0_en and sq0_on). The <em>active</em> bit is set and cleared e.g. when the length counter is loaded and reaches zero, respectively. The <em>active</em> bit also seems to be what you get back from $4015 reads, which suggests that overflow isn't simply clearing it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />I can't read the decaps either. All I've done so far is to trace node values.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5911">ulfalizer</a> on Wed May 01, 2013 5:25 pm, edited 1 time in total.</span>
						<br clear="all" /><br />

