			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For future reference and in case anyone wants to experiment, here's how to confirm that the square channel is silenced when the timer &lt; 8. (It only tests the first pulse channel, but it'd be weird if the second one was different.)<br /><br />Edit: Confirmed that the second pulse channel works the same way.<br /><br />Test program:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">// Enable pulse<br />LDA #$01&nbsp; &#91;A9 01&#93;<br />STA $4015 &#91;8D 15 40&#93;<br />// Set pulse volume, use constant volume<br />LDA #$1F&nbsp; &#91;A9 1F&#93;<br />STA $4000 &#91;8D 00 40&#93;<br />// Set pulse timer low<br />LDA #$08&nbsp; &#91;A9 08&#93;<br />STA $4002 &#91;8D 02 40&#93;<br />// Set pulse length counter and timer high (to zero)<br />LDA #$F8&nbsp; &#91;A9 F8&#93;<br />STA $4003 &#91;8D 03 40&#93;<br />// Loop endlessy<br />CLC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&#91;18&#93;<br />BCC #$FE&nbsp; &#91;90 FE&#93;</div><br /><br />Corresponding Visual 2A03 URL:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/visual2a03/?graphics=false&amp;logmore=Execute,sq0_en,sq0_on,sq0_p,sq0_t,sq0_out&amp;a=0&amp;d=a9018d1540a91f8d0040a9088d0240a9f88d03401890fe">http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/v ... 03401890fe</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><em>a=0d=a901...</em> puts the program at address 0. <em>logmore</em> specifies some nodes to trace (a list of nodes can be found in nodenames.js). When run, you only see sq0_out ever being non-zero if the timer &gt;= 8.<br /><br />Edit: A guess would be that the output condition is something like <em>active bit set</em> <strong>AND</strong> <em>timer &gt;= 8</em> <strong>AND NOT</strong> <em>carry out from sweep unit addition</em>. The sweep unit period update condition might be just the last two. I wonder if Quietust could confirm this and maybe add some node names...</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

